task.summary: Still quite janky, but camera output is no longer upside-down.

Reorganised code structure of server.py so that it's server-based.
It now executes command from server rather than from client.

Added support for deep learning models.
Currently, it only supports Yolov5.
YoloManager can now draw bounding boxes

Server and Client are now a distinct class
Livestreaming feature is usable, but more testing is required.
Previously assumed that there was an issue with box/keypoints visualisation, but turned out that the model was predicting the wrong keypoints. This was fixed.
Custom Sort algorithm now works with Yolov5.
Footage can be livestreamed from server to client. The client will apply SORT and visualise the results.
Bounding box and its associated keypoints are drawn at different iterations. This is fixed.
Added MovementManager that's responsible for Pepper's basic locomotion.

Restructured models folder.
OCSort Manager implemented, but is not working properly at the moment.
OCSort drawing incorrect bounding box fixed. Turns out scale was completely irrelevant, so it was deleted.

For:
yolo.py: - added the ability to save bounding box data as a .csv
sort.py: - added the ability to read .csv bounding box data and superimpose tracking over clean images

Restructured folders
Messed around with sys.path to avoid import errors
OCSORT works within the server-client system with Pepper.
